# Language Requirements

## English-Only Policy

**ALL code, comments, and documentation MUST be in English only.**

### This Applies To

- ✅ Code comments (inline, block, JSDoc)
- ✅ Variable names, function names, class names
- ✅ User-facing messages (bot replies, error messages)
- ✅ Documentation (README, API docs, inline docs)
- ✅ Commit messages
- ✅ Configuration files and comments
- ✅ Test descriptions and assertions
- ✅ Log messages
- ✅ Dockerfile comments
- ✅ Environment variable names

### Forbidden

- ❌ Russian language (Cyrillic characters)
- ❌ Any non-English language in code or comments
- ❌ Mixed language comments (e.g., English + Russian)

### Examples

#### ✅ Correct

```typescript
// Calculate total sales amount
const calculateTotalSales = (
  cashAmount: number,
  cardAmount: number
): number => {
  return cashAmount + cardAmount;
};

// Log the result
logger.info("Total sales calculated successfully");
```

#### ❌ Incorrect

```typescript
// Вычисляем общую сумму продаж
const calculateTotalSales = (nalichnye: number, karta: number): number => {
  return nalichnye + karta;
};

// Логируем результат
logger.info("Продажи рассчитаны успешно");
```

## Rationale

- Ensures code is accessible to international developers
- Maintains consistency across the entire codebase
- Facilitates code reviews and collaboration
- Professional standard for open-source projects
- Better compatibility with AI assistants and tooling
